CHAPTER IV.-That property sure to be taken is not held as taken and required by the enemy.

Cephalus holds that “a thing is called captured when it can not escape capture,” and he applies this dictum to a certain case ol pirates. Molina applies it to wild beasts which have been injured by one hunter and ultimately taken by another.
